rComments: The best! His lectures are very clear and organized. He breaks difficult concepts down to manageable pieces and he is VERY available for students who seek help.
He is the best. Orgo is not easy but he just has a way of making it doable. Great prof.

He is just awesome, one of the best prof ever! He explains the concept super clearly and helps are always available. He made me love organic chemistry so much. His British accent made me concentrate more in class. Definitely would highly recommend this prof

I love this guy! Honestly the CHM247 lecturing team is BOMB!! Such great teachers who evidently care for students. Whenever I pass Prof D's office, his door is always open. Also, his accent made me pay more attention to what he was saying, and he overall has excellent presentation skills. I was lucky enough to have him for CHM136 and CHM247.

He is my hero. Always gives a talk after every midterm and he will literally inspire you to do good on the next midterm. Very good lectures that are clear and concise. Covers difficult topics very smoothly and a generally nice and jolly person. Please take his Organic Chem classes, he's the definition of Sweetermans.
Great prof!!! Made me enjoy organic chemistry in comparison to the prof I had for CHM136. Funny prof and his explanations are extremely clear and easy to follow.
Great lectures, though tests are somewhat tricky.

He made me like organic chemistry again. After dealing with Professor Browning last year I thought I was hopeless, but Professor D changed that. Go to class. His lectures are awesome. He explains everything so well. His test will definitely test you on some fine details, but if you go to class and work for it you'll do great.

Probably one of the best profs out there, awesome lectures, very clear, gives you helpful study tips and tricks for remembering things during lecture. On the whole, an awesome guy and an awesome prof.

He's a great prof in so many ways. If I had him for the entirety of the course I guarantee I would have gotten an A+. He makes it so his lectures easy to stay focused and he's very clear on what he expects you to know for the tests.
Awesome lecturer but real tough test, I took his class last year, still haunts my dreams.

He is excellent at explaining concepts in organic chemistry clearly. It's really easy to understand some complicated concepts as he breaks them down nicely and explains it in steps. However, I find his test questions are really hard. His questions are very tricky and require a lot of application.

Best prof of the lot in CHM136. Really made concepts clear and did a good job of keeping the class engaged. He's pretty funny (even worse a banana suit to class for Halloween) and he clearly outlines what will be tested in tests. Would definitely recommend!
He was one of the best CHM profs I ever had. Organized, clear and simply outstanding in teaching. His questions are very fair. Amazing prof.
Best lecturer in chemistry, hard questions but fair.
He explains concepts in organic chemistry very clearly and makes it easier to understand. However, despite this, his test papers are not easy to crack!
Very clear in lectures. Explains the chemistry quite well. Pretty funny too at times. British accent to top it off.
Great would be an underestimation. He teaches the Canadian Olympiad team for chemistry. Go to office hours.
I honestly looked forward to his lectures. I don't even like chem that much but damn this prof was good at making me forget that. 11/10 I'm gonna try take more of his lectures in the future
An amazing lecturer! Super funny and friendly, really cares about the course. Make sure to come up to him after class if you don't understand something, he will help you 100%.
Genuinely just a nice British prof that makes learning at UofT (dare I say) fun.

Very very good prof, extremely engaging and takes a personal interest in your progress. Gives students the option to schedule personal meetings outside of class to discuss "paths to success". Clear, concise teaching, and also clear on what he expects from students.  Tests may be construed as difficult if you wing it, but generally not difficult
He sparked my interest in organic chem and was always there for extra help
He's one of those profs who'll ask how you're doing and encourage you to ask him questions. Extremely engaging and an excellent professor.

Okay so get ready to cry a whole lot unless you are ABSOLUTELY in love with organic chemistry.  10% of the content is like high school orgo, but the rest of it is just a complete and utter mess of concepts and visualisations.  Read the textbook. Go to class. GO TO YOUR TUTORIAL. Memorise those reaction mechanisms.

rComments: So far my favorite professor at UofT. Really funny, super clear in his lectures and he really cares about the class. All around great guy.
Great guy, great sense of humour, probably my favourite professor so far at U of T. He's also very helpful, and is willing to hold in pee to explain a concept to you in the hallway.
He is a great professor, but he talks a lot during his lectures, so there is little time for you to copy down the information. He has a British accent.

When I came into this course, I remember nothing from grade 12 chem. Dr. D made chem fun with his energy and enthusiasm. His pacing was good and he leaves some blanks in his power point slides so you actually have to take some notes.
The most amazing professor with excellent notes. His enthusiasm and patience is really commendable. He makes one of the toughest courses at Uoft, very fun and enjoyable.
Clever, clear and interesting. Really connects the basis of organic to the real world and is passionate about his work.
Explains concepts well, tests were fair. Exam was tough

He is an amazing professor ! He will truly take time to help you with anything and he is a very patient person. You can really see the passion he puts forth in teaching this course and helping first years.
Very clear, made me want to go to class, very helpful

Explains concepts very well, takes time to go over past test questions and answers students' questions after class. He makes jokes, keeps class interested and makes organic chem fun to learn. He is passionate about teaching orgo, he keeps the class engaged and overall he is a very jolly fellow. I would take other chem courses with him as well
Best prof you'll have in first year. His smile is epic!! Never miss his class, they are the best!
